headline: GE HealthCare Alliances And MRI Approvals Deepen Imaging Revenue Potential
summary: GE HealthCare Technologies (NasdaqGS:GEHC) announced a 10 year alliance with UCSF Health to roll out advanced imaging solutions across the UCSF network. The company entered a commercial collaboration with Gentuity LLC to broaden access to high frequency OCT imaging in interventional cardiology. GE HealthCare received FDA clearance for three MRI products, adding new options to its medical imaging portfolio.
